The paper deals with game theory and optimization in the context of linear congestion games with altruistic social context. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.GT (Game Theory and Economics). The paper also involves multi-agent systems and decision-making, which suggests cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) as another likely category. The paper also involves the study of equilibrium and stability, which suggests cs.DS (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) as possible categories. Finally, the paper involves optimization and linear programming, which suggests cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as a possible category.
